                            <comment id="417718" author="adilger" created="Fri, 14 Jun 2024 00:01:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;I think this test is not very robust.  Firstly, it is using &lt;tt&gt;[ $((old_iused - new_iused)) -gt 400 ]&lt;/tt&gt; for the numeric comparison instead of &lt;tt&gt;(( old_iused - new_iused &amp;gt; 400 ] ))&lt;/tt&gt;, so it looks like it fails most of the time because the number of objects &lt;b&gt;decreased&lt;/b&gt; (i.e. negative difference) since the start of the test:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/426720d0-057c-4837-9d06-ff94edc60903&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/426720d0-057c-4837-9d06-ff94edc60903&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;waited 120 sec, old Iused 5084, new Iused 4748
waited 120 sec, old Iused 5551, new Iused 5183
waited 120 sec, old Iused 6617, new Iused 6249
waited 120 sec, old Iused 4007, new Iused 3639
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This should be fixed with a simple patch and avoid most of the failures.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, it also isn&apos;t clear if the test is totally robust, because it is creating files before &lt;tt&gt;max_create_count=0&lt;/tt&gt; is set, but the MDS may start creating new objects before all of the precreated OST objects are consumed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Sometimes it is reporting a failure for unknown reasons, when it should be within the 400-object limit:&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/cfb9000f-df2c-4a1f-bf8a-7bbd29604460&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/cfb9000f-df2c-4a1f-bf8a-7bbd29604460&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;waited 120 sec, old Iused 2025, new Iused 2105
waited 120 sec, old Iused 3877, new Iused 4149
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;and other times it appears that the &quot;&lt;tt&gt;old_iused&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; value returned zero, so &quot;df&quot; wasn&apos;t working or something (b2_14 servers in interop?):&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1fd4e85b-a5bc-467f-ba14-6b12a1832eb6&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/1fd4e85b-a5bc-467f-ba14-6b12a1832eb6&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/44fe3a1c-1540-4e1a-a970-ef591f7db166&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/sub_tests/44fe3a1c-1540-4e1a-a970-ef591f7db166&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;waited 120 sec, old Iused 1000, new Iused 1712
waited 120 sec, old Iused 1000, new Iused 1715
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
